sql:
SELECT pair_name, pair_description
FROM currency_pairs
WHERE pair_id = 1;

SELECT trader_name
FROM traders
ORDER BY trader_name ASC;

external_knowledge:
- Bullish trends refer to trends with descriptions starting with 'Bullish';
- Bearish trends refer to trends with descriptions starting with 'Bearish';
- The latest trends are determined by the highest trend_end value for each currency pair;
- The latest market data is determined by the highest local_time value for each currency pair;
- The latest predictions are determined by the highest prediction_date value for each currency pair.

sql:
SELECT trader_name
FROM traders
ORDER BY trader_name;

external_knowledge:
- Average confidence level greater than seventy percent means the trader's overall confidence in their predictions is high; 
- Top three profit ranking means the trader has at least one prediction with high profit or low loss; 
- Top three accuracy ranking means the trader has at least one prediction with low absolute difference between predicted and actual prices.

sql:
SELECT report_date
FROM regulatory_reports
WHERE currency_pair = 'EUR/USD';

external_knowledge:
- "Most profitable" refers to the sessions with the highest profit/loss values; 
- "Trend at the time" implies that the trend description is relevant to the time period of the trading session; 
- "Price forecast" refers to the predicted price of the currency pair during the trading session; 
- "Actual price" represents the actual price of the currency pair during the trading session, which may differ from the predicted price.
